  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto, com.poesys.db.dto.IObserver, com.poesys.db.dto.ISubject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto>, IPageView

    public class PageView
extends AbstractPageView

    A data-access layer data-transfer object for the PageView. This class is the concrete subclass of the generated abstract class. Make any changes to DTO behavior by overriding methods here rather than changing the abstract superclass; AndroMDA will overwrite that class when you run it but will never overwrite this concrete subclass.

    A single access of a URI for a given IP address at a given date and time; may be part of a session if it has a session id

    Stereotypes:

    • Persistent
    • SequenceKey

        public PageView(com.poesys.db.pk.IPrimaryKey key,

        java.lang.String uri,
        java.lang.String ip,
        java.lang.String sessionId,
        java.math.BigInteger partyId)

        Create a PageView. This constructor calls the abstract superclass constructor.

        Parameters:
        key - the primary key of the PageView
        pageViewId - primary key attribute
        pageViewDate - the date and time of the page view request
        uri - the request URI and any query string
        ip - the IP address of the requests in the session; all page views in the session have this IP address
        sessionId - a token identifying a collection of page views as defined by the client processing the page views
        partyId - foreign key used by setter to query associated object
